{{stub}}
Missions are Cataclysm's "quests". They are assigned at the start of the game, by NPCs, or occasionally triggered during the game.

== Game Start Missions==
These missions are assigned at game start. The reward for completion is a mood boost.

===Background Missions===
Missions assigned when you choose a character background.
{| class="wikitable" style="width: 100%; "
! style="width: 33; "|Mission
! style="width: 33; "|Background
! style="width: 33; "|Description
! style="width: 33; "|Requirements
|-
!Find some cosplay suits
|Background: Cosplay
|The world could have ended, but there are still some fantastic costumes out there, just waiting for you to wear them. Search them until you find them.
|Find and wear one of many costumes available in the world.
|-
!Dress with style
|Background: Modeling
|You need to always dress in style and fashion. Find a gown or tuxedo for your personal use.
|Wear a tuxedo or evening gown.
|-
!Find a tabletop game
|Background: Role-playing
|As a Game Master, it's just unacceptable that you now lack your means to play. Find any tabletop game to play with any survivors you could find, even a cards game will suffice.
|Obtain one of: D&amp;D, Battlehammer, Battlehammer 40K, deck of cards, Magic cards, chess, checkers, Pictionary, Catan, Battleship, or Clue.
|-
!Find some skates
|Background: Skating, Roller Derby, Roller Hockey
|You are a skater at heart, and as such you need some skates to drive by, any kind will suffice.
|Wear roller skates, roller blades, or heelys.
|-
|}

===Challenge &amp; Scenario Missions===
Missions assigned when you choose an opening scenario.
{| class="wikitable" style="width: 100%; "
! style="width: 33; "|Mission
! style="width: 33; "|Background
! style="width: 33; "|Description
! style="width: 33; "|Requirements
|-
!Kill your pursuer
|Challenge: Hunted
|Since the start of the Cataclysm, something has been hunting you relentlessly. You can outrun it but never truly escape it. It won't end until one of you dies.
|
|-
!Ready or Not
|Challenge: Mansion Escape
|Survive all day from the crazy inhabitants of the mansion.
|Completes at midnight of the first day.
|-
!Return to base
|Scenario: Helicopter Crash
|Your helicopter was crashed to the ground, communications were lost with ground base, and the rest of your team died while landing, at least you still know the way back to the base.
|Go to the location highlighted on your map.
|-
!Find Antibiotics Before You Die!
|Scenario: Infected
|
|
|-
!Refuel your helicopter.
|Scenario: Last Flight
|You were flying towards a nearby private airport before your forced landing. You could still reach it by ground, and scavenge it for fuel
|An airport is highlighted on your map. Go there and bring back fuel for your helicopter. Can also be fulfilled by obtaining and starting a new helicopter.
|-
!Reach The Mansion And Finish This Delivery
|Scenario: The Last Delivery
|Go to the mansion highlighted on your map.
|-
|}

=== Profession Missions ===
These are the missions that come with specific professions.
{| class="wikitable" style="width: 100%; "
! style="width: 33; "|Mission
! style="width: 33; "|Profession
! style="width: 33; "|Description
! style="width: 33; "|Requirements
|-
!Kill your mark
|Profession: Assassin (Prison Start)
|Your employer could be no longer responding but you have decided to finish your mission. Hunt down and kill your mark.
|Go to the marked location on your map and kill the target there.
|-
!Finish your mission
|Profession: Assassin, Hitman
|Your mission required you to eliminate a certain high-ranking individual in hiding. Your mark seems to have turned feral while escaping and the world appears to be ending, but not even that can stop you from finishing your mission.
|Go to the marked location on your map and kill the target there. 
|-
!Hunt big game
|Profession: Bow Hunter, Crossbow Hunter, Modern Archer, Rifle Hunter, Shotgun Hunter
|The end of the world could have arrived, but you still crave for that one big hunt. Search and kill a black bear to remember the old days.
|Kill a Bear.
|-
!Social butterfly
|Profession: Cheerleader, Major General, Career Politician, Mafia Boss
|You have always had good social abilities. Go and recruit 2 followers and establish your leadership among them. Don't forget to order them to build a base of operations for you in the form of a survivor camp.
|Have 2 NPC allies and create a faction camp.
|-
!Prepare for your next show
|Profession: Clown
|Become the best clown, make sure that your next show will make everyone laugh by training your social skills to perfection.
|
|-
!Protect your canine friends
|Profession: Dog Lover
|You have saved your dogs from the fall of the world, but they could still suffer from danger everywhere. Police dogs used some Kevlar harnesses for protection… Maybe your friends could use some too?
|
|-
!Find a memory of your master
|Profession: Lost Submissive
|Find and wield a whip to remember your master even when separated.
|Wield a whip.
|-
!Make the cops pay
|Profession: Mafia Boss
|They wanted to put you behind bars, but are now dead, make them pay with blood, unliving blood.
|
|-
!Obtain your black belt
|Profession: Martial Artist, Novice Martial Artist
|You could have become a master in martial arts if you had the chance, so train until you achieve the level of a master in the old world, and find yourself a nice black belt to commemorate the occasion.
|
|-
!Go to the refueling stop
|Profession: Military Pilot
|Your bird is now on the ground, never again able to fly, you could search for a new one in the closest refueling stop requisitioned by the military.
|
|-
!Kill your rivals
|Profession: Ninja
|As a real ninja, you can't allow competitors for the night. Kill 10 shady zombies and demonstrate who is the real ninja here.
|Kill 10 Shady Zombie.
|-
!Become the protagonist
|Profession: Otaku
|The world has become like an anime! Zombies, mutants, the end of civilization as we know it… You must become the protagonist if you want to survive, the plot armor will help you. Go and kill 50 zombies to show your protagonist potential.
|Kill 50 Zombie.
|-
!Life vow
|Profession: Patient
|Live your life to the fullest, prove to yourself that you can survive this new obstacle in the same way that you have survived the last.
|
|-
!Recover a part of yourself
|Profession: Portal Traveler
|They took away something from you, something important. You feel a connection with this weather, maybe you can recover some portion of what you lost in one of these storms.
|
|-
!Find a real katana
|Profession: Urban Samurai
|The world has ended, but as an authentic samurai you lack a katana, you must find one, quickly.
|Obtain a Katana.
|-
!Continue with your evolution
|Profession: Volunteer Mutant
|Your evolution to a more perfect form was interrupted by the Cataclysm. Restart your transformation process whatever it costs.
|Use mutagen to obtain the "Changing" status effect.
|-
|}

== Starting NPC Missions ==
In some scenarios, your character starts near another NPC, which may offer one or more missions. 
{| class="wikitable" style="width: 100%; "
! style="width: 20; "|Mission
! style="width: 20; "|Questgiver
! style="width: 20; "|Description
! style="width: 20; "|Offer
! style="width: 20; "|Goal
! style="width: 20; "|Reward
|-

!Find Corporate Accounts
|NPC (Corporate) 1
|Those twisted snakes…
|Our world fell apart because our leaders were as crooked as the con-men that paid for their elections. Just find me one of those corporate accounting books and I'll show you and the rest of the world just who is at fault.
|Go to the marked location and find a corporate accounting book; return with it to the NPC.
|Relationship; trade, training; follow-up mission available.
|-
!Retrieve Deposit Box
|NPC (Corporate) 2
|Now I don't mean to upset you but I'm not sure what I can do with the accounting ledger at the moment. We do have a new lead though, the ledger has a safe deposit box under the regional manager's name. Guess what, dumb sucker wrote down his combination. Come with me to retrieve the box and you can keep any of the goodies in it that I can't use to press charges against these bastards.
|
|Find the safety deposit box and return it to the NPC.
|Relationship; trade, training; follow-up mission available.
|-
!Find Deputy Badge
|NPC (Corporate) 3
|I hope you will find use from what you got out of the deposit box but I also have another job for you that might lead you to an opportunity to deal out justice for those who cannot. First things first, we can't just look like ruffians. Find us a deputy badge, easy enough?
|
|Find a deputy's badge. They can be found at police stations.
|Relationship; trade, training.
|-
!Find Patient Records
|NPC (Medical) 1
|I've lost so many friends… please find me a patient list from the regional hospital or doctor's office.  I just want to know who might still be out there.
|Go to the hospital marked on your map and bring back the patient records. Hospitals are dangerous locations; be careful.
|Relationship; trade, training; follow-up mission available.
|-
!Reach FEMA Camp
|NPC (Medical) 2
|Maybe they escaped to one of the camps…
|I can't thank you enough for bringing me the patient records but I do have another request.  You seem to know your way around… could you take me to one of the FEMA camps?  I know some were overrun but I don't want to believe all of them could have fallen.
|Go to the FEMA camp marked on your map.
|Relationship; trade, training; follow-up mission available.
|-
!Reach Farm House
|NPC (Medical) 3
|I just need a place to start over…
|'ve accepted that everyone I used to know is dead… one way or another.  I really wish I could have done something to save my brother but he was one of the first to go.  I'd like to start over, just rebuild at one of the farms in the countryside.  Can you help me secure one?"
|Go to the farmhouse marked on your map.
|Relationship; trade, training. NPC may leave your party to stay at the farmhouse.
|-
!Find Flag
|NPC (Patriot) 1
|Does our flag still yet wave? We're battered but not yet out of the fight, we need the old colors!
|Does our flag still yet wave? We're battered but not yet out of the fight, we need the old colors!
|Find an American Flag and bring it back to the NPC.
|Relationship; trade, training; follow-up mission available.
|-
!Retrieve Military Black Box
|NPC (Patriot) 2
|We've got the flag, now we need to locate US forces.
|We have the flag but now we need to locate US troops to see what we can do to help. I haven't seen any but I'm figurin' one of those choppers that were flyin' round during th' outbreak would have a good idea. If you can get me a black box from one of the wrecks I'll look into where we might open 'er at.
|Return to the NPC with a Black Box.
|Relationship; trade, training; follow-up mission available.
|-
!Retrieve Black Box Transcript
|NPC (Patriot) 3
|With the black box in hand, we need to find a lab.
|Thanks to your searching we've got the black box but now we need to have a look inside her. Now, most buildings don't have power anymore but there are a few that might be of use. Have you ever seen one of those science labs that have popped up in the middle of nowhere? Them suckers have a glowing terminal out front so I know they have power somewhere inside 'em. If you can get inside and find a computer lab that still works you ought to be able to find out what's in the black box.
|Explore a lab, use a terminal to read the black box and print out a transcript; return to the NPC with it.
|Relationship; trade, training; follow-up mission available.
|-
!Follow Sarcophagus Team
|NPC (Patriot) 4
|Holy hell, the crash you recovered the black box from wasn't as old as I thought. Check this out, it was on its approach to pick up a team sent to secure and destroy something called a 'Hazardous Waste Sarcophagus' in the middle of nowhere. If the bird never picked up the team then we may still have a chance to meet up with them. It includes an access code for the elevator and an encoded message for the team leader, I guess. If we want to join up with what remains of the government then now may be our only chance.
|
|Go to the location marked on your map. The NPC will join your team.
|Relationship; trade, training.
|-
!Find Relic
|NPC (Religious) 1
|As the world seems to abandon the reality that we once knew, it becomes plausible that the old superstitions that were cast aside may have had some truth to them. Please go and find me a religious relic… I doubt it will be of much use but I've got to hope in something.
|
|Go to the marked location and bring back the Small Relic found there.
|Relationship; trade, training; follow-up mission available.
|-
!Recover Priest's Diary
|NPC (Religious) 2
|From what I understand, the creatures you encountered surrounding this relic were unlike anything I've heard of. It is laughable that I now consider the living dead to be part of our ordinary reality. Never-the-less, the church must have some explanation for these events. I have located the residence of a local clergy man, could you go to this address and recover any items that may reveal what the church's stance is on these events?
|
|Go to the house marked on your map and return with the priest's diary.
|Relationship; trade, training; follow-up mission available.
|-
!Investigate Cult
|NPC (Religious) 3
|You have no idea how interesting this diary is. I have two very promising leads… first things first, the Catholic Church has been performing its own investigations into global cult phenomenon and it appears to have become very interested in a local cult as of recently. Could you investigate a location for me? I'm not sure what was going on here but the priest seemed fairly worried about it.
|
|Go to the location marked on your map and return with an etched skull.
|Relationship; trade, training; follow-up mission available.
|-
!Prison Visionary
|NPC (Religious) 4
|I have another task if you are feeling up to it. There is a prisoner that the priest made special mention of. I was wondering if you could see what may have happened to him or if he left anything in his cell. The priest admits the individual is rather unstable, to put it lightly, but the priest personally believed the man was some kind of repentant visionary. I'm not in a position to cast out the account just yet… it seems the man has prophesied events accurately before concerning the Church of Starry Wisdom.
|
|Go to the location marked on your map and return with the book "Visions in Solitude".
|Relationship; trade, training.
|-

!Kill Jabberwock
|NPC (Zombie Hunter) 1
|A few days ago another survivor and I were trying to avoid the cities by staying in the woods during the day and foraging for gear at night. It worked well against the normal zed's but one night something caught onto our trail and chased us for ten minutes or so until we decided to split up and meet-up back here. My buddy never showed up and I don't have the means to kill whatever it was. Can you lend a hand?
|
|Go to the marked location and kill the Jabberwock.
|Relationship; trade, training; follow-up mission available.
|-
!Kill 100 Zombies
|NPC (Zombie Hunter) 2
|You're kitted out better than most… would you be interested in making this world a little better for the rest of us? The towns have enough supplies for us survivors to start securing a foothold but we don't have anyone with the skills and equipment to thin the masses of undead. I'll lend you a hand to the best of my ability but you really showed promise taking out that other beast. You, I, and a 100 zombies laid to rest, what do you say?
|
|Kill 100 regular zombies.
|Relationship; trade, training; follow-up mission available.
|-
!Kill Horde Master
|NPC (Zombie Hunter) 3
|Apparently one of the other survivors picked up on an unusually dense horde of undead moving into the area. At the center of this throng there was a 'leader' of some sort. The short of it is, kill the son of a bitch. We don't know what it is capable of or why it is surrounded by other zombies but this thing reeks of trouble. Do whatever it takes but we can't risk it getting away.
|
|Go to the marked location and kill the Horde Master.
|Relationship; trade, training; follow-up mission available.
|-
!Recruit Tracker
|NPC (Zombie Hunter) 4
|We've got another problem to deal with but I don't think we can handle it on our own. So, I sent word out and found us a volunteer… of sorts. He's vain as hell but has a little skill with firearms. He was supposed to collect whatever he had of value and is going to meet us at a cabin in the woods. Wasn't sure how long we were going to be so I told him to just camp there until we picked him up.
|
|Go to the marked location and talk to the NPC there.
|Relationship; trade, training; follow-up mission available.
|-
!Find Deputy Badge
|NPC (Zombie Hunter) 5 Tracker
|I got the brief so I know what I'm getting into. Let me be upfront, treat me like shit and I'm going to cover my own hide. However, you treat me well and give me something to believe in, even if it's just a shiny bit of metal, and I'll do you right. Without a strong band a man doesn't stand a chance in this world. You ready to take charge boss? This world could use a Sheriff just about now.
|
|Bring a deputy badge to the Tracker.
|Relationship; trade, training. The Tracker will join your party.
|-
!Analyze Zombie Blood
|NPC
|I need someone to get a sample of zombie blood, take it to a hospital, and perform a centrifuge analysis of it.
|
|
|
|-
!Angry pyromaniac
|NPC
|I'm so **** infuriated! I've got an enemy that ruined my life, and now I want to get revenge! I don't care about the Cataclysm, I just want to burn his house! Would you help me, [Player Name]?
|
|The NPC will start following you. Obtain some gasoline and go to the house indicated.
|Relationship; trade or training.
|-
!Break into armory to retrieve family photo
|NPC
|I need you to get my family photo from the armory safe.
|
|
|
|-
!Find Antibiotics
|NPC
|This infection is bad, very bad…
|I'm infected. Badly. I need you to get some good antibiotics for me…
|Find Antibiotic and return to the NPC with it within 2 days.
|Relationship; trade or training.
|-
!Find Inhaler
|NPC
|I'm… short… of breath…
|I'm asthmatic. I need you to get an inhaler for me…
|Find an inhaler and return to the NPC with it.
|Relationship; trade or training.
|-
!Find Lost Dog
|NPC
|I left my poor dog in a house, not far from here. Can you retrieve it?
|
|Go to the location marked on your map. Use the whistle given to you by the NPC to get the dog to follow you and return to the NPC with it.
|Relationship; trade or training.
|-
!Find Weather Log
|NPC
|Everyone who dies gets back up, right? Which means that whatever is causing this it must be airborne to have infected everyone. I believe that if that is the case then there should be regions that were not downwind from where-ever the disease was released. We need to find a record of all the weather patterns leading up to the outbreak.
|
|Go to the radio station marked on your map and return with the weather log found there.
|Relationship; trade or training. 
|-
!Gather cattail stalks to create cattail jelly
|NPC
|Gather 80 cattail stalks from the swamp and bring them back to learn how to craft cattail jelly. Raise your survival skill to at least 1 by harvesting cattail stalks. Bring back the provided bag as well.
|Medical services are a little sparse following the Cataclysm, but people have been surviving using their wits and the bounty of Mother Nature for a long time. Care to learn a little?
|Be holding 80 cattail stalks and the duffel bag the survivor gave you and have a Survival skill of 1 or higher.
|Learn cattail jelly recipe.
|-
!Kill Zombie Mom
|NPC
|My mom… she's… she was killed, but then she just got back up… she's one of those things now. Can you put her out of her misery for me?
|
|Go to the location on the map and kill the named zombie.
|Relationship; trade or training. Spiritual NPCs will get a mood boost for building a coffin and burying the named zombie.
|-
!Prove your worth to Foodperson
|NPC
|Show me the proof of your loyalty to the great Foodplace, and I'll consider you worthy of my friendship. Ten loyalty cards should be enough, I'm sure you already have much more than that waiting for you at home, right?
|
|Find 10 Foodplace Loyalty Cards. They can often be found in wallets.
|Relationship; trade, training.
|-
!Prove You're A Survivor
|NPC
|Prove you're a survivor by surviving for 10 days after the Cataclysm, and then returning to the person who gave you this mission.
|It's hard surviving out here on our own, and we'd probably have a better chance working together.  Problem is, I don't really know you and what you're capable of.  You might have what it takes, or you might not.  Either way, I'm going to need some proof.  Come back in a few days and I'll gladly follow you.  It's basically a win-win for me: either you come back and I'll know you've got what it takes, or you don't and I'll know that I was right not to follow you.
|Survive for 10 days, then talk to the NPC.
|NPC will join you; trade or training.
|-
!Retrieve Software
|NPC
|There's some important software on my computer that I need on USB.
|
|Take the USB given to you by the NPC, go to the house marked on your map, use the terminal there to download the software, and bring it back to the NPC.
|Relationship, trade, or training.
|-
|}
== Exodii Missions ==
The Exodii are plane-hopping scavenger cyborgs living in a castle made of junk. They offer CBM installation services.
{| class="wikitable" style="width: 100%; "
! style="width: 20; "|Mission
! style="width: 20; "|Questgiver
! style="width: 20; "|Description
! style="width: 20; "|Offer
! style="width: 20; "|Goal
! style="width: 20; "|Reward
|-
!Follow the directions on the pictographic sign
|Examining the sign
|I found a weird pictographic sign that seemed to point towards someone willing to trade.
|This is a sign with a series of simple line-art pictograms showing what appears to be a basic trade transaction. A pair of hands offers a piece of some kind of junk, and another pair of hands offers a small pouch in return.
|Go to the location on your map
|Meet the Exodii
|-
!Bring 1000 units of anesthetic to Rubik
|Rubik
|
|If'n us'll to add the metal an' plastic for ye, us'll need a thousand unit o' them anus-feticks, half for your thinkin'-meat an' half for our stock.
|Bring 1000 Anesthetic
|Installation of basic CBMs.
|-
!Investigate the Mysterious Bunker
|Rubik
|
|
|Go to the Refugee Center marked on your map and return.
|Meet the Free Merchants and the refugee center inhabitants.
|-
|}
== Holdouts Missions ==
Various NPCs are holed up in cabins and other locations. They may give quests or offer services.

{| class="wikitable" style="width: 100%; "
! style="width: 20; "|Mission
! style="width: 20; "|Questgiver
