! Reach Refugee Center
| [Choose the "Contact Us" option on the Evac Shelter computer.]
| n/a
| Go to the refugee center (highlighted on your map).
| n/a
|-
! Alonso must have his special pants
| Alonso Lautrec
| I think I might know where those special pants might be though… (Alonso got drunk, crashed a party, and lost his pants. He wants them back.)
| Bring Alonso one pair of leather pants. The location indicated on your map is an adult bookstore, but any pair of leather pants will do.
| Alonso will now offer you his escort services if you have a condom.
|-
! Find someone to clean up the back bay.
| Boris Borichenko Mission 1
| Boris in the refugee center is looking for at least five people to help clear up the back bay.
| Get five people to agree to help with the job. Guneet Singh, Aleesha Seward, Garry Villenueve, Uyen Tran, Rhyzaea Johnny, and the Old Guard Representative can be persuaded. The Teamster will agree without persuasion, and Smokes can be given either 5 or 10 Merch to hire the guards to help; 10 Merch will hire two guards and Smokes will also agree.
|5 Merch; relationship, trade, or training.
|-
! Bring Boris a circular saw.
| Boris Borichenko Mission 2
| We now have a space to work in, and I have wood and nails to spare.  All I need is a saw.  I would love tablesaw and mitre saw, but I can work with a hand held circular saw for now.  I have looked, and what we have is garbage.  Can you bring me a good one?
|Talk to Boris with a Circular Saw in your inventory.
|5 Merch; relationship, trade, or training. Boris will now sell training in Carving, Basic Carpentry, and Plumbing.
|-
!Bring Boris his son's lost writing.
| Boris Borichenko Mission 3
| If you can find it, it would mean so much to me.  I will give you directions to the shelter where he left it.  It was barely a shelter, broken and torn apart.  It should just be on the floor where it was dropped.
| Go to the location marked and pick up Ash's Laptop Computer. Return it to Boris.
|5 Merch; relationship, trade, or training.
|-
!Find Dana's family sourdough culture
| Dana Nunez, after buying some of her sourdough bread, or trading her flour for bread.
| If you really like this second-rate bread, you could risk your life for something actually worth it.  I left my actual sourdough starter back in the bakery where I worked.  That baby is a hundred years old, and has been in my family for generations. If you can bring him to me, I'll bake you the finest bread you've ever had.
|Go to location highlighted on the map, a bakery, and bring back Dana's family sourdough starter.
|After a 14-day wait, Dana will start to sell high-quality sourdough bread.
|-
! Bring 40 small cardboard boxes
| Dino Dave, Mission 1
| Gotta start small right?  Little ones for keeping little things safe.  I could use 'em.  I need a bunch of 'em.  Little ones, you know?  Can you bring me like… like… forty?
| Bring Dave 40 of the item "small cardboard box".
| Unlocks mission "Bring a roll of duct tape".
|-
! Bring a roll of duct tape
| Dino Dave, Mission 2
| These ones are good, good ones.  They need something to, you know, bind them together.  Surround them, light side, dark side.  Bring me the Force!
| Bring Dave 200 units of Duct Tape.
| Unlocks mission "Bring 10 Cardboard Boxes".
|-
! Bring 10 cardboard boxes
| Dino Dave, Mission 3
| Ten bigger ones now please.  The list doesn't lie.  You've done so well.  I got a little more on the list, but we're more than half there.
| Bring Dave 10 of the item "Cardboard Box".
| Unlocks mission "Bring 10 large plastic sheets".
|-
! Bring 10 large plastic sheets
| Dino Dave, Mission 4
| If I can set it up in here I won't need it, but they might drive me out, so I guess I need some plastic just in case.  I don't like it, the sandman can smell through plastic, but I think the cardboard is stronger.
| Bring Dave 10 of the item "Large Plastic Sheet". They can be found, among other places, by deconstructing the ground sheets at mass graves.
| Unlocks mission "Bring 5 large cardboard boxes"
|-
! Bring 5 large cardboard boxes
| Dino Dave, Mission 5
| This is the last thing I need from you.  I've been collecting the other parts myself, it's been easier with more cardboard around.  Can you bring me five more really big cardboard boxes?
| Bring Dave 5 "Large Cardboard Box". These can be taken down where found and folded and unfolded via crafting to make them easier to haul; unfolding them takes duct tape to glue them back together.
| Dino Dave builds his cardboard mansion; the other beggars see you as trustworthy.
|-
